<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Samuel 4:1-22</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="31">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="22">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And the word of Samuel continued to come to all Israel.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs1-2">Then Israel went out to meet the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines in battle; and they took up camping alongside Eb&middot;en&middot;e&acute;zer, and the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines themselves encamped in A&acute;phek.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines proceeded to draw up in formation to meet Israel, and the battle went badly, so that Israel was defeated before the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines, who went striking down about four thousand men in closed battle line in the field.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">When the people came to the camp the older men of Israel began to say: “Why did Jehovah defeat us today before the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines? Let us take to ourselves from Shi&acute;loh the ark of Jehovah’s covenant, that it may come into our midst and may save us from the palm of our enemies.”</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">So the people sent to Shi&acute;loh and carried from there the ark of the covenant of Jehovah of armies, who is sitting upon the cherubs. And the two sons of E&acute;li were there with the ark of the covenant of the [true] God, namely, Hoph&acute;ni and Phin&acute;e&middot;has.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And it came about that as soon as the ark of the covenant of Jehovah came into the camp, all the Israelites broke out into loud shouting, so that the earth was in a stir.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">The Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines also got to hear the sound of the shouting and began saying: “What does the sound of this loud shouting in the camp of the Hebrews mean?” Finally they got to know that the ark of Jehovah itself had come into the camp.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines became afraid, because, they said: “God has come into the camp!” So they said: “Woe to us, for such a thing as this never occurred before!</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">Woe to us! Who will save us from the hand of this majestic God? This is the God that was the smiter of Egypt with every sort of slaughter in the wilderness.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Show yourselves courageous and prove yourselves men, <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines, that <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> may not serve the Hebrews just as they have served <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>; and <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> must prove yourselves men and fight!”</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Accordingly the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines fought and Israel was defeated, and they went fleeing each one to his tent; and the slaughter came to be very great, so that out of Israel there fell thirty thousand men on foot.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And the ark of God itself was captured, and the two sons of E&acute;li, Hoph&acute;ni and Phin&acute;e&middot;has, died.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And a man of Benjamin went running from the battle line so that he arrived at Shi&acute;loh on that day with his garments ripped apart and dirt on his head.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">When he arrived, there was E&acute;li sitting on the seat by the roadside, watching, because his heart had become atremble over the ark of the [true] God. And the man himself went in to report in the city, and the whole city began crying out.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And E&acute;li got to hear the sound of the outcry. So he said: “What does the sound of this turmoil mean?” And the man himself hurried that he might go in and report to E&acute;li.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">(Now E&acute;li was ninety-eight years old, and his eyes had set so that he was unable to see.)</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And the man proceeded to say to E&acute;li: “I am the one coming from the battle line, and I—it is from the battle line that I have fled today.” At this he said: “What is the thing that has happened, my son?”</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">So the news bearer answered and said: “Israel has fled before the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines, and there has also occurred a great defeat among the people; and also your own two sons have died—Hoph&acute;ni and Phin&acute;e&middot;has—and the very ark of the [true] God has been captured.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">And it came about that at the moment that he mentioned the ark of the [true] God, he began to fall from the seat backward beside the gate, and his neck got broken so that he died, because the man was old and heavy; and he himself had judged Israel forty years.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And his daughter-in-law, the wife of Phin&acute;e&middot;has, was pregnant near to giving birth, and she got to hear the report that the ark of the [true] God was captured and that her father-in-law and her husband had died. At that she bowed herself and began giving birth, because her pangs came unexpectedly upon her.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And about the time of her death, the women standing by her began to speak: “Do not be afraid, because it is a son that you have borne.” And she did not answer and did not set her heart on it.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">But she called the boy Ich&acute;a&middot;bod, saying: “Glory has gone away from Israel into exile,” [this] with reference to the ark of the [true] God’s being captured and with reference to her father-in-law and her husband.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">So she said: “Glory has gone away from Israel into exile, because the ark of the [true] God has been captured.”</span>
</p>
</form>

