<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Samuel 5:1-12</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="31">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="12">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">As for the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines, they took the ark of the [true] God and then brought it from Eb&middot;en&middot;e&acute;zer to Ash&acute;dod.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines proceeded to take the ark of the [true] God and bring it into the house of Da&acute;gon and station it beside Da&acute;gon.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">Then the Ash&acute;dod&middot;ites got up early the very next day, and there Da&acute;gon was fallen upon his face to the earth before the ark of Jehovah. So they took Da&acute;gon and returned him to his place.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">When they got up early in the morning the very day after, there Da&acute;gon was fallen upon his face to the earth before the ark of Jehovah, with the head of Da&acute;gon and the palms of both his hands cut off, to the threshold. Only the fish part had been left upon him.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">That is why the priests of Da&acute;gon and all those going into the house of Da&acute;gon do not tread upon the threshold of Da&acute;gon in Ash&acute;dod down to this day.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And the hand of Jehovah came to be heavy upon the Ash&acute;dod&middot;ites, and he began causing panic and striking them with piles, namely, Ash&acute;dod and its territories.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And the men of Ash&acute;dod came to see that it was so, and they said: “Do not let the ark of the God of Israel dwell with us, because his hand has been hard against us and against Da&acute;gon our god.”</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">Consequently they sent and gathered all the axis lords of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines to them and said: “What shall we do to the ark of the God of Israel?” Finally they said: “Toward Gath let the ark of the God of Israel go around.” So they brought the ark of the God of Israel around to there.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And it came about that after they had brought it around to there, the hand of Jehovah came to be upon the city with a very great confusion, and he began striking the men of the city, from small to great, and piles began breaking out on them.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Hence they sent the ark of the [true] God to Ek&acute;ron. And it came about that as soon as the ark of the [true] God came to Ek&acute;ron, the Ek&acute;ron&middot;ites began to cry out, saying: “They have brought the ark of the God of Israel around to me to put me and my people to death!”</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">Consequently they sent and gathered all the axis lords of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines and said: “S<span class="smallcaps">END</span> the ark of the God of Israel away that it may return to its place and may not put me and my people to death.” For a death-dealing confusion had occurred in the whole city; the hand of the [true] God had been very heavy there,</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">and the men that did not die had been struck with piles. And the cry of the city for help kept ascending to the heavens.</span>
</p>
</form>

