<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Samuel 7:1-17</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="31">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="17">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Accordingly the men of Kir&acute;i&middot;ath-je&acute;a&middot;rim came and brought the ark of Jehovah up and took it into the house of A&middot;bin&acute;a&middot;dab on the hill, and El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar his son was the one whom they sanctified to guard the ark of Jehovah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And it came about that from the day of the Ark’s dwelling in Kir&acute;i&middot;ath-je&acute;a&middot;rim the days kept multiplying, so that they amounted to twenty years, and all the house of Israel went lamenting after Jehovah.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And Samuel proceeded to say to all the house of Israel: “If it is with all <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> heart <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> are returning to Jehovah, put away the foreign gods from <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> midst and also the Ash&acute;to&middot;reth images, and direct <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> heart unswervingly to Jehovah and serve him alone, and he will deliver <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> from the hand of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines.”</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">At that the sons of Israel put away the Ba&acute;als and the Ash&acute;to&middot;reth images and began serving Jehovah alone.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Then Samuel said: “Collect all Israel together at Miz&acute;pah, that I may pray in <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> behalf to Jehovah.”</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">So they were collected together at Miz&acute;pah, and they went drawing water and pouring it out before Jehovah and kept a fast on that day. And they began saying there: “We have sinned against Jehovah.” And Samuel took up judging the sons of Israel in Miz&acute;pah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines came to hear that the sons of Israel had collected themselves together at Miz&acute;pah, and the axis lords of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines got on their way up against Israel. When the sons of Israel heard of it, they began to be afraid on account of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">So the sons of Israel said to Samuel: “Do not keep silent for our sakes from calling to Jehovah our God for aid, that he may save us from the hand of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines.”</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Then Samuel took a sucking lamb and offered it up as a burnt offering, a whole offering, to Jehovah; and Samuel began calling to Jehovah for aid in behalf of Israel, and Jehovah proceeded to answer him.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">And it came about that while Samuel was offering up the burnt offering, the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines themselves drew near for battle against Israel. And Jehovah now caused it to thunder with a loud noise on that day against the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines, that he might throw them into confusion; and they got defeated before Israel.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">At that the men of Israel sallied forth from Miz&acute;pah and went in pursuit of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines and kept striking them down as far as south of Beth-car.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">Then Samuel took a stone and set it between Miz&acute;pah and Jesh&acute;a&middot;nah and began to call its name Eb&middot;en&middot;e&acute;zer. Accordingly he said: “Till now Jehovah has helped us.”</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">Thus the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines were subdued, and they did not come anymore into the territory of Israel; and the hand of Jehovah continued to be against the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines all the days of Samuel.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And the cities that the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines had taken from Israel kept coming back to Israel from Ek&acute;ron to Gath, and the territory of them Israel delivered from the hand of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs14-2">And there came to be peace between Israel and the Am&acute;or&middot;ites.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And Samuel kept on judging Israel all the days of his life.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And he traveled from year to year and made the circuit of Beth&acute;el and Gil&acute;gal and Miz&acute;pah and judged Israel at all these places.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">But his return was to Ra&acute;mah, because there was where his house was, and there he judged Israel. And he proceeded to build an altar there to Jehovah.</span>
</p>
</form>

