<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Samuel 14:1-52</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="31">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="52">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And it came about one day that Jon&acute;a&middot;than the son of Saul proceeded to say to the attendant carrying his weapons: “Do come and let us cross over to the outpost of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines who are across over there.” But to his father he did not tell it.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And Saul was dwelling at the outskirts of Gib&acute;e&middot;ah under the pomegranate tree that is in Mig&acute;ron; and the people that were with him were about six hundred men.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">(And A&middot;hi&acute;jah the son of A&middot;hi&acute;tub, the brother of Ich&acute;a&middot;bod, the son of Phin&acute;e&middot;has, the son of E&acute;li, the priest of Jehovah in Shi&acute;loh, was carrying the eph&acute;od.) And the people themselves did not know that Jon&acute;a&middot;than had gone.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Now between the passages that Jon&acute;a&middot;than looked for to cross over against the outpost of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines there was a toothlike crag here on this side and a toothlike crag there on that side, and the name of the one was Bo&acute;zez and the name of the other was Se&acute;neh.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">The one tooth was a pillar on the north facing Mich&acute;mash, and the other was on the south facing Ge&acute;ba.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">So Jon&acute;a&middot;than said to the attendant, his armor-bearer: “Do come and let us cross over to the outpost of these uncircumcised men. Perhaps Jehovah will work for us, for there is no hindrance to Jehovah to save by many or by few.”</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">At this his armor-bearer said to him: “Do whatever is in your heart. Turn where you wish to. Here I am with you in accord with your heart.”</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">Then Jon&acute;a&middot;than said: “Here we are crossing over to the men, and let us expose ourselves to them.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">If this is the way they should say to us, ‘Stand still until we make contact with <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>!’ we must then stand where we are, and we should not go on up to them.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">But if this is the way they should say, ‘Come up against us!’ we must then go up, because Jehovah will certainly give them into our hand, and this is for us the sign.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">With that the two of them exposed themselves to the outpost of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines. And the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines proceeded to say: “Here are the Hebrews coming out from the holes where they have hidden themselves.”</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">So the men of the outpost answered Jon&acute;a&middot;than and his armor-bearer and said: “Come on up to us, and we will let <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> know a thing!” At once Jon&acute;a&middot;than said to his armor-bearer: “Come up after me, because Jehovah will certainly give them into the hand of Israel.”</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And Jon&acute;a&middot;than kept going up on his hands and his feet, and his armor-bearer after him; and they began to fall before Jon&acute;a&middot;than, and his armor-bearer was putting them to death behind him.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And the first slaughter with which Jon&acute;a&middot;than and his armor-bearer struck them down amounted to about twenty men within about half the plowing line in an acre of field.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">Then a trembling occurred in the camp in the field and among all the people of the outpost; and the force of pillagers trembled, even they, and the earth began quaking, and it developed into a trembling from God.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And the watchmen belonging to Saul in Gib&acute;e&middot;ah of Benjamin got to see it, and, look! the turmoil swayed this way and that.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">And Saul proceeded to say to the people that were with him: “Take the count, please, and see who has gone out from us.” When they took the count, why, look! Jon&acute;a&middot;than and his armor-bearer were not there.</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">Saul now said to A&middot;hi&acute;jah: “Do bring the ark of the [true] God near!” (For the ark of the [true] God proved to be on that day with the sons of Israel.)</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And it came about that while Saul was speaking to the priest, the turmoil that was in the camp of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines continued to go on, getting greater and greater. Then Saul said to the priest: “Withdraw your hand.”</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">Thus Saul and all the people that were with him were called out. So they came as far as the battle, and there the sword of each one had come to be against his fellowman; the rout was very great.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">And the Hebrews that had come to belong to the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines as formerly and that had gone up with them into the camp round about, even they too were for proving themselves to be with Israel who was with Saul and Jon&acute;a&middot;than.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">All the men of Israel also that were hidden in the mountainous region of E&acute;phra&middot;im heard that the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines had taken to flight, and they too went pursuing closely after them into the battle.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">And Jehovah proceeded on that day to save Israel, and the battle itself passed over to Beth-a&acute;ven.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">And the men of Israel themselves were hard pressed on that day, and yet Saul put the people under the pledge of an oath, saying: “Cursed is the man that eats bread before the evening and until I have taken vengeance upon my enemies!” And none of the people tasted bread.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">And all those of the land came into the woods, when honey happened to be over all the surface of the field.</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">When the people came into the woods, why, look! there was a dripping of honey, but there was no one putting his hand to his mouth, because the people were afraid of the oath.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">As for Jon&acute;a&middot;than, he had not been listening when his father put the people under an oath, so he stretched out the tip of the rod that was in his hand and dipped it into the honeycomb and drew his hand back to his mouth, and his eyes began to beam.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">At this one of the people answered and said: “Your father solemnly put the people under oath, saying, ‘Cursed is the man that eats bread today!’” (And the people began to get tired.)</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">However, Jon&acute;a&middot;than said: “My father has brought ostracism upon the land. S<span class="smallcaps">EE</span>, please, how my eyes have beamed because I tasted this little bit of honey.</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">How much more so if the people had but eaten today from the spoil of their enemies that they found! For now the slaughter upon the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines has not been great.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">And on that day they kept striking down the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines from Mich&acute;mash to Ai&acute;ja&middot;lon, and the people got to be very tired.</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">And the people began darting greedily at the spoil and taking sheep and cattle and calves and slaughtering them on the earth, and the people fell to eating along with the blood.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">So they told Saul, saying: “Look! The people are sinning against Jehovah by eating along with the blood.” At this he said: “Y<span class="smallcaps">OU</span> have dealt treacherously. First of all, roll a great stone to me.”</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">After that Saul said: “Scatter among the people, and <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> must say to them, ‘Bring near to me, each one of <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>, his bull and, each one, his sheep, and <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> must do the slaughtering in this place and the eating, and <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> must not sin against Jehovah by eating along with the blood.’” Accordingly all the people brought near each one his bull that was in his hand that night and did the slaughtering there.</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">And Saul proceeded to build an altar to Jehovah. With it he started altar building to Jehovah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">Later Saul said: “Let us go down after the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines by night and plunder them until the morning lightens up, and let us not leave a single one among them.” To this they said: “Anything that is good in your eyes do.” Then the priest said: “Let us approach here to the [true] God.”</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">And Saul began to inquire of God: “Shall I go down after the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines? Will you give them into the hand of Israel?” And he did not answer him on that day.</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">So Saul said: “Come near here, all <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> keymen of the people, and ascertain and see in what way this sin has come to be today.</span> <a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">For as Jehovah, who is the Deliverer of Israel, is alive, even if it is in Jon&acute;a&middot;than my son, yet he will positively die.” But there was no one answering him out of all the people.</span> <a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">And he went on to say to all Israel: “Y<span class="smallcaps">OU</span> yourselves will come to be on the one side, and I and Jon&acute;a&middot;than my son—we will come to be on the other side.” At this the people said to Saul: “What is good in your eyes do.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk41" class="vsAnchor">41</a>
       <span id="vs41">And Saul proceeded to say to Jehovah: “O God of Israel, do give Thum&acute;mim!” Then Jon&acute;a&middot;than and Saul were taken, and the people themselves went out.</span> <a name="bk42" class="vsAnchor">42</a>
       <span id="vs42">Saul now said: “C<span class="smallcaps">AST</span> lots to decide between me and Jon&acute;a&middot;than my son.” And Jon&acute;a&middot;than got to be taken.</span> <a name="bk43" class="vsAnchor">43</a>
       <span id="vs43">Then Saul said to Jon&acute;a&middot;than: “Do tell me, What have you done?” So Jon&acute;a&middot;than told him and said: “I did for a fact taste a little honey on the tip of the rod that is in my hand. Here I am! Let me die!”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk44" class="vsAnchor">44</a>
       <span id="vs44">At this Saul said: “Thus may God do and thus may he add to it, if you do not positively die, Jon&acute;a&middot;than.”</span> <a name="bk45" class="vsAnchor">45</a>
       <span id="vs45">But the people said to Saul: “Is Jon&acute;a&middot;than to die, who has performed this great salvation in Israel? It is unthinkable! As Jehovah is alive, not as much as a single hair of his head will fall to the earth; for it was with God that he worked this day.” With that the people redeemed Jon&acute;a&middot;than, and he did not die.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk46" class="vsAnchor">46</a>
       <span id="vs46">So Saul withdrew from following the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines, and the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines themselves went to their place.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk47" class="vsAnchor">47</a>
       <span id="vs47">And Saul himself took the kingship over Israel and went warring round about against all his enemies, against Mo&acute;ab and against the sons of Am&acute;mon and against E&acute;dom and against the kings of Zo&acute;bah and against the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines; and wherever he would turn he administered condemnation.</span> <a name="bk48" class="vsAnchor">48</a>
       <span id="vs48">And he went on acting valiantly and proceeded to strike down Am&acute;a&middot;lek and to deliver Israel out of the hand of their pillager.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk49" class="vsAnchor">49</a>
       <span id="vs49">And the sons of Saul came to be Jon&acute;a&middot;than and Ish&acute;vi and Mal&acute;chi-shu&acute;a, and, as for the names of his two daughters, the name of the one born first was Me&acute;rab and the name of the younger one Mi&acute;chal.</span> <a name="bk50" class="vsAnchor">50</a>
       <span id="vs50">And the name of Saul’s wife was A&middot;hin&acute;o&middot;am the daughter of A&middot;him&acute;a&middot;az, and the name of the chief of his army was Ab&acute;ner the son of Ner, the uncle of Saul.</span> <a name="bk51" class="vsAnchor">51</a>
       <span id="vs51">And Kish was the father of Saul, and Ner the father of Ab&acute;ner was the son of A&middot;bi&acute;el.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk52" class="vsAnchor">52</a>
       <span id="vs52">And the warfare continued heavy against the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines all the days of Saul. When Saul saw any mighty man or any valiant person, he would gather him to himself.</span>
</p>
</form>

