<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Samuel 22:1-23</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="31">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="23">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">So David proceeded to go from there and escape to the cave of A&middot;dul&acute;lam; and his brothers and the entire house of his father got to hear of it and made their way down there to him.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And all men in distress and all men who had a creditor and all men bitter in soul began to collect together to him, and he came to be a chief over them; and there came to be with him about four hundred men.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">Later David went from there to Miz&acute;peh in Mo&acute;ab and said to the king of Mo&acute;ab: “Let my father and my mother, please, dwell with <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> people until I know what God will do to me.”</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Accordingly he settled them before the king of Mo&acute;ab, and they continued dwelling with him all the days that David happened to be in the inaccessible place.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">In time Gad the prophet said to David: “You must not keep dwelling in the inaccessible place. Go away, and you must come yourself into the land of Judah.” Hence David went away and came into the forest of He&acute;reth.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And Saul got to hear that David and the men that were with him had been discovered, while Saul was sitting in Gib&acute;e&middot;ah under the tamarisk tree on the high place with his spear in his hand and all his servants stationed about him.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">Then Saul said to his servants stationed about him: “Listen, please, <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> Ben&acute;ja&middot;min&middot;ites. Will the son of Jes&acute;se also give to all of <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> fields and vineyards? Will he appoint all of <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> chiefs of thousands and chiefs of hundreds?</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">For <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> have conspired, all of <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>, against me; and there is no one disclosing it to my ear when my own son concludes [a covenant] with the son of Jes&acute;se, and there is no one of <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> having sympathy for me and disclosing to my ear that my own son has raised up my own servant against me as a lier in ambush the way it is this day.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">At this Do&acute;eg the E&acute;dom&middot;ite, being stationed as he was over the servants of Saul, answered and said: “I saw the son of Jes&acute;se come to Nob to A&middot;him&acute;e&middot;lech the son of A&middot;hi&acute;tub.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">And he proceeded to inquire of Jehovah for him; and provisions he gave him, and the sword of Go&middot;li&acute;ath the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tine he gave him.”</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">At once the king sent to call A&middot;him&acute;e&middot;lech the son of A&middot;hi&acute;tub the priest and all the house of his father, the priests that were in Nob. So all of them came to the king.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">Saul now said: “Listen, please, you son of A&middot;hi&acute;tub!” to which he said: “Here I am, my lord.”</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And Saul went on to say to him: “Why have <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> men conspired against me, you and the son of Jes&acute;se, by your giving him bread and a sword, and there being an inquiry of God for him, to rise up against me as a lier in ambush the way it is this day?”</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">At this A&middot;him&acute;e&middot;lech answered the king and said: “And who among all your servants is like David, faithful, and the son-in-law of the king and a chief over your bodyguard and honored in your house?</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">Is it today that I have started to inquire of God for him? It is unthinkable on my part! Do not let the king lay anything against his servant [and] against the entire house of my father, for in all this your servant did not know a thing small or great.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">But the king said: “You will positively die, A&middot;him&acute;e&middot;lech, you with all the house of your father.”</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">With that the king said to the runners stationed about him: “Turn and put to death the priests of Jehovah, because their hand also is with David and because they knew that he was a runaway and they did not disclose it to my ear!” And the servants of the king did not want to thrust out their hand to assault the priests of Jehovah.</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">Finally the king said to Do&acute;eg: “You turn and assault the priests!” Immediately Do&acute;eg the E&acute;dom&middot;ite turned and himself assaulted the priests and put to death on that day eighty-five men bearing an eph&acute;od of linen.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">Even Nob the city of the priests he struck with the edge of the sword, man as well as woman, child as well as suckling and bull and ass and sheep with the edge of the sword.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">However, one son of A&middot;him&acute;e&middot;lech the son of A&middot;hi&acute;tub, whose name was A&middot;bi&acute;a&middot;thar, made his escape and went running away to follow David.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">Then A&middot;bi&acute;a&middot;thar told David: “Saul has killed the priests of Jehovah.”</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">At this David said to A&middot;bi&acute;a&middot;thar: “I well knew on that day, because Do&acute;eg the E&acute;dom&middot;ite was there, that he would without fail tell Saul. I personally have wronged every soul of the house of your father.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">Just dwell with me. Do not be afraid, for whoever looks for my soul looks for your soul, for you are one needing protection with me.”</span>
</p>
</form>

