<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Samuel 29:1-11</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="31">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="11">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines proceeded to collect all their camps together at A&acute;phek, while the Israelites were camping by the spring that was in Jez&acute;re&middot;el.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And the axis lords of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines were passing along by hundreds and by thousands, and David and his men were passing along afterward with A&acute;chish.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And the princes of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines began to say: “What do these Hebrews mean?” At this A&acute;chish said to the princes of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines: “Is this not David the servant of Saul king of Israel, who happened to be with me here a year or two, and I have not found in him a single thing from the day of his deserting [to me] until this day?”</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And the princes of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines became indignant at him; and the princes of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines went on to say to him: “Make the man go back, and let him go back to his place where you assigned him; and do not let him go down with us into the battle, that he may not become a resister of us in the battle. And with what should this person put himself in favor with his lord? Is it not with the heads of those [our] men?</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Is this not David to whom they kept responding in the dances, saying, ‘Saul has struck down his thousands, and David his tens of thousands’?”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">Consequently A&acute;chish called David and said to him: “As Jehovah is living, you are upright, and your going out and your coming in with me in the camp has been good in my eyes; for I have not found badness in you from the day of your coming to me until this day. But in the eyes of the axis lords you are not good.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And now return and go in peace, that you may not do anything bad in the eyes of the axis lords of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines.”</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">However, David said to A&acute;chish: “Why, what have I done, and what have you found in your servant from the day that I came to be before you until this day, that I should not come and actually fight against the enemies of my lord the king?”</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">At this A&acute;chish answered and said to David: “I well know that you have been good in my own eyes, like an angel of God. Only it is the princes of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines that have said, ‘Let him not go up with us into the battle.’</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">And now rise up early in the morning with the servants of your lord that came with you; and <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> men must rise up early in the morning when it has become light for <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>. Then go.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">Accordingly David rose up early, he and his men, to go in the morning and return to the land of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines; and the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines themselves went up to Jez&acute;re&middot;el.</span>
</p>
</form>

