<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Samuel 31:1-13</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="31">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="13">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Now the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines were fighting against Israel, and the men of Israel took to flight from before the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines, and they kept falling down slain in Mount Gil&middot;bo&acute;a.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines kept in close range of Saul and his sons; and the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines at last struck down Jon&acute;a&middot;than and A&middot;bin&acute;a&middot;dab and Mal&acute;chi-shu&acute;a, Saul’s sons.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And the fighting became heavy against Saul, and the shooters, the bowmen, finally found him, and he got severely wounded by the shooters.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Then Saul said to his armor-bearer: “Draw your sword and run me through with it, that these uncircumcised men may not come and certainly run me through and deal abusively with me.” And his armor-bearer was unwilling, because he was very much afraid. So Saul took the sword and fell upon it.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">When his armor-bearer saw that Saul had died, then he too fell upon his own sword and died with him.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">Thus Saul and his three sons and his armor-bearer, even all his men, came to die together on that day.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">When the men of Israel that were in the region of the low plain and that were in the region of the Jordan saw that the men of Israel had fled, and that Saul and his sons had died, then they began to leave the cities and flee, after which the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines came on in and took up dwelling in them.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And it came about the next day that, when the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines came to strip the slain, they got to find Saul and his three sons fallen upon Mount Gil&middot;bo&acute;a.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And they proceeded to cut off his head and strip off his armor and send into the land of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines all around to inform the houses of their idols and the people.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Finally they put his armor in the house of the Ash&acute;to&middot;reth images, and his corpse they fastened on the wall of Beth-shan.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And as regards him, the inhabitants of Ja&acute;besh-gil&acute;e&middot;ad got to hear what the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines had done to Saul.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">Immediately all the valiant men rose up and went all night long and took the corpse of Saul and the corpses of his sons off the wall of Beth-shan and came to Ja&acute;besh and burned them there.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">Then they took their bones and buried them under the tamarisk tree in Ja&acute;besh, and they went fasting for seven days.</span>
</p>
</form>

